The talks between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership were concluded in mid-November.
This months-long and difficult-to-translate Freenet game is part of the consolidation of the German telecommunications market.
At the end of the third quarter, Freenet had 2,9 million mobile subscribers and 1,27 million customers with full or DSL connections.
United Internet Holding and Drillische previously held a 6.01% stake in Freenet.
Now it's been agreed that Drillisch will get approximately another 4%.
The right to buy 18,49% of the investment company Vatas was agreed as early as August.
